HEADWORD: Zohar
<hw>Zo"har</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb.
<ets>z⟦omac⟧har</ets> candor, splendor.]</ety> <def>A Jewish cabalistic
book attributed by tradition to Rabbi <person>Simon ben Yochi</person>,
who lived about the end of the 1st century, <sc>a. d.</sc> Modern critics
believe it to be a compilation of the 13th century.</def> <rj><au>Encyc.
Brit.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
